improved disaster recovery and backup capabilities. These benefits make cloud computing an attractive
option for SMEs, as it enables them to access advanced technologies and resources without significant
upfront investments.

## Factors Affecting Cloud Computing Adoption in SMEs

Several factors have been identified as significant in the adoption of cloud computing by SMEs. Kumar
et al. (2017) found that perceived benefits, top management support, competitive pressure, and perceived
concerns play a crucial role in cloud computing adoption. Furthermore, Lutfi (2022) conducted a study
in Sabah, Malaysia, and identified cost saving, top management support, and technology readiness as
the main factors affecting cloud computing adoption by SMEs in that region. These findings emphasize
the importance of organizational support, perceived benefits, and technological readiness in driving the
adoption of cloud computing among SMEs.

## Knowledge Gaps and Future Research Directions

Despite the growing adoption of cloud computing by MSMEs, there are still knowledge gaps that
need to be addressed. First, empirical research on cybersecurity risk management in SMEs is needed
(Semanticscholar.org). This research gap indicates the need for further investigation into cybersecurity
practices and strategies specifically tailored to the needs and capabilities of MSMEs. Second, while this
literature review focuses on the comparison of cybersecurity threats and practices in the cloud context
among MSMEs, there is a need for more in-depth studies examining the specific challenges and best
practices for cloud security in different industries and sectors.
Future research should prioritize the investigation of cybersecurity issues and practices in the context of
cloud computing, taking into account the differences among MSMEs. This includes considering factors
such as organizational capabilities, IT resources, external pressure, competition and government, ICT
providers and firm departments, employee and managerial factors, data security, technology readiness,
top management support, competitive pressure, and innovation. Additionally, research should explore the
specific benefits of cloud computing for different types of SMEs and industries, as well as the factors
influencing the adoption of cloud computing in different regions and countries.

## Conclusion

In conclusion, this literature review compared critical cybersecurity threats and practices in the context of
cloud computing among MSMEs. The findings highlight the importance of organizational capabilities, IT
resources, external pressure, competition and government, ICT providers and firm departments, employee
and managerial factors, data security, technology readiness, top management support, competitive pressure, and innovation in driving the adoption of cloud computing among MSMEs. The benefits of cloud
computing for SMEs include cost advantage, easy deployment process, access to the latest technologies,
